Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.31,0:00:04.91,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.91,0:00:07.02,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Was this designed to be impossible?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.56,0:01:52.50,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.51,0:01:58.34,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.64,0:02:05.52,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1654,1)}Guild Master
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:03.52,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Guild Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.23,0:02:09.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is that even right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.07,0:02:13.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Three raid bosses at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.17,0:02:15.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.59,0:02:18.40,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What was that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.79,0:02:21.66,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is this the only place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.73,0:02:24.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.58,0:02:27.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If all the other raid zones are like this now...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.14,0:02:30.67,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.67,0:02:35.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Winning a raid will become impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.93,0:02:40.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What were we working so hard for?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.54,0:02:44.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We trained, got good equipment, \Nand worked together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.35,0:02:46.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We failed and tried again...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.61,0:02:50.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When it worked, it felt great.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.25,0:02:52.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I felt like I'd grown.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.63,0:02:55.82,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,That's all gone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.56,0:02:58.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.54,0:02:59.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.89,0:03:02.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No point in doing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.41,0:03:05.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The game has abandoned us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.58,0:03:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Elder Tale{\i0} has abandoned us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.84,0:03:13.12,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So what is this good for, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.59,0:03:13.12,Default - flashback,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,A game, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.12,0:03:15.62,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A PC game in this day and age?\NAren't social games good enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.62,0:03:17.09,Default - flashback,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You stay at home on weekends?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.09,0:03:18.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Screw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.82,0:03:21.28,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I bet no one ever invites you to karaoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.28,0:03:23.50,Default - flashback,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Then you talk to your PC, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.50,0:03:25.95,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why not get a hobby that'll be \Nmore useful to your future?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.95,0:03:27.81,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there are some people like that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.81,0:03:28.60,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.92,0:03:29.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Screw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:38.48,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What am I supposed to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.35,0:03:41.49,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,"We can win next time, so let's do our best"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:44.39,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,"The other raid zones will be okay"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.42,0:03:46.36,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Those are lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.72,0:03:48.11,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.99,0:03:50.32,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.32,0:03:51.49,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then what does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.99,0:03:54.29,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Does this mean we're—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.29,0:03:56.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.72,0:04:06.37,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we can go back to Susukino,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.37,0:04:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and be a good peacekeeping guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.60,0:04:12.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That might not be so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.28,0:04:14.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Ezzo has a lot of monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.07,0:04:17.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The People of the Land will thank us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.92,0:04:20.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I can get one of them to be my girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.94,0:04:25.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That might be the smart way to live...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.25,0:04:27.76,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.02,0:04:30.66,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But doesn't that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.34,0:04:33.41,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,make us no different from them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.98,0:04:35.94,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Those bastards who acted like they knew it all
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.94,0:04:39.88,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,while they gave us advice we were \Nsupposed to be so thankful for?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.74,0:04:41.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.54,0:04:46.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I think you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.03,0:04:48.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But what of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.59,0:04:50.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Screw it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.63,0:04:53.80,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,William?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.98,0:04:56.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.59,0:04:57.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We got wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.39,0:05:00.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We may be finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.34,0:05:01.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was all a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.18,0:05:04.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Like they always said...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:09.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're idiots who've wasted our time \Non something as pointless as games.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.52,0:05:11.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Game junkies who never leave their houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.65,0:05:12.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.67,0:05:15.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.60,0:05:17.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We knew that all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:20.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We knew it, and we do it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:23.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But we love games.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.56,0:05:25.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We chose this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.75,0:05:27.26,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if this is the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.60,0:05:30.03,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't give this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.43,0:05:32.71,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There are some things you just can't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.54,0:05:35.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.32,0:05:37.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,All we did was lose in a raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.76,0:05:39.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That happens all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.28,0:05:42.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to be shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.96,0:05:47.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,All it means is that another bit of win-loss data
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.52,0:05:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is recorded on the server.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.79,0:05:54.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Games are what children play.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.11,0:05:56.26,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.26,0:05:58.37,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They were special to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:03.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I won't tell you it's time to grow \Nup and head back to town.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.74,0:06:05.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let anyone else say it, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.85,0:06:09.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We may be maggots, losers who got beat...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.59,0:06:12.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't let anyone, not even God, \Ntell me it was a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:14.03,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.41,0:06:16.39,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,For me, they were the center of the universe!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.02,0:06:21.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What do the bits recorded on the server matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.15,0:06:23.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.24,0:06:25.15,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've decided they matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.52,0:06:29.91,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And I've decided that they're \Nwonderful, glorious things!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.76,0:06:36.16,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The idiots who believe that God \Nhas decided exactly what matters,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.16,0:06:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that it applies to every single \Nperson, won't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.27,0:06:42.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how stupid it looks,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.41,0:06:44.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,no matter how fake and gilded it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.59,0:06:47.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,if I—if we—decide it's amazing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.96,0:06:49.38,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,then it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.90,0:06:51.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that what it means to choose?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.48,0:06:55.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We chose to be here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.13,0:06:58.68,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let anyone insult that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.69,0:07:02.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We've spent a lot of time in {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.35,0:07:05.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A very long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.93,0:07:08.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A powerful foe has appeared here,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.07,0:07:11.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and we'll take swords or bows or \Nwhatever we've got, and charge at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.85,0:07:14.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll scream and charge at it like children!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.72,0:07:19.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And sometimes we'll win, and sometimes we'll lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.22,0:07:25.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, it's all a bunch of bits on a server, \Nswitching between one and zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.02,0:07:27.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.04,0:07:31.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We've dedicated our lives to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.20,0:07:33.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And that's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.91,0:07:36.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we win, we'll have a huge victory party.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.73,0:07:39.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll each take our share of the \Nphantasmals and have a toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.71,0:07:41.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we lose, we'll get upset,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.49,0:07:44.98,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and spend the whole day talking \Nabout what we did wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.49,0:07:47.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to say it's stupid, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.95,0:07:50.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter if it's a toy, or if it's all fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:52.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We think it's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.93,0:07:55.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We've decided to spend our time on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.68,0:07:57.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So it's real!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.49,0:08:04.66,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So we lost the raid...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.05,0:08:07.75,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Something sacred and inviolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.58,0:08:10.14,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.64,0:08:11.65,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.17,0:08:14.19,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I say to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.54,0:08:15.76,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What can I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.05,0:08:18.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Because that's what we are, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.37,0:08:21.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's who we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.45,0:08:24.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about the people who have everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.60,0:08:26.71,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.06,0:08:28.75,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What am I saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.39,0:08:32.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,People who know how to live in harmony with others
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.32,0:08:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can have anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.65,0:08:37.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,so they can live their lives that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.25,0:08:38.78,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What am I talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.06,0:08:42.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you guys have something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.10,0:08:43.31,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.31,0:08:44.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.02,0:08:48.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Something that allows you to go \Nanywhere and befriend anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.79,0:08:51.80,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But this is all I have left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.09,0:08:53.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It can be intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.93,0:08:55.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It can be coolness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.20,0:08:57.96,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It can be a bright personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.96,0:08:59.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It can be funny jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.50,0:09:01.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It can be anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.89,0:09:06.93,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have anything that lets \Nyou shine in the real world?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.39,0:09:08.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.91,0:09:10.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Not a single thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.08,0:09:15.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've never told anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.89,0:09:17.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.04,0:09:20.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But you guys are my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.15,0:09:26.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Without the game, I wasn't able to make friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.89,0:09:28.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so lame...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.89,0:09:30.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.96,0:09:34.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I've made it this far because I had the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.54,0:09:39.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand your feelings \Nbecause I had the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.52,0:09:45.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm playing, I can tell that \None of you wants healing,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.54,0:09:49.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,or one guy who's posted in the back \Nwants to be in the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.02,0:09:54.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Or that she's too shy to say so,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.09,0:09:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but she wants that bracelet that boosts magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.71,0:10:00.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.98,0:10:03.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That this guy cares about his comrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.62,0:10:06.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Or that this guy's scared, but he's \Ntrying to yell as hard as he can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.40,0:10:11.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Or that someone's tired, but they forced \Nthemselves to log in anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.53,0:10:13.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.70,0:10:17.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I really can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.33,0:10:20.54,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.06,0:10:24.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Elder Tale {\i1}has taught me many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.62,0:10:28.63,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how other people think.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.23,0:10:30.76,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm self-righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.76,0:10:32.11,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Uncaring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.50,0:10:34.02,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Uncooperative.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.02,0:10:35.62,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I give up too easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.62,0:10:37.08,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I can't read moods.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.75,0:10:40.03,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't try to get involved with other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.81,0:10:44.43,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I was told for so long,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.93,0:10:47.79,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I started to refuse to be with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.10,0:10:52.48,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But in {\i0}Elder Tale{\i1}, even someone like me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.48,0:10:55.30,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,was able to connect with others a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.76,0:10:59.19,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And as long as I cared about them,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.19,0:11:02.33,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,{\i0}Elder Tale{\i1} taught me many secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.26,0:11:05.52,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The first thing I learned was teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.07,0:11:07.80,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Some people did well at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.80,0:11:09.28,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Some people did horribly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.72,0:11:11.38,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Some were talented.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.38,0:11:12.81,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Some sucked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.75,0:11:18.03,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But what mattered was working with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.96,0:11:20.90,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even when I thought someone was terrible,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.90,0:11:24.08,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,sometimes I just didn't understand \Nwhat they were trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.65,0:11:27.63,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And then I started doing raids.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.48,0:11:31.65,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason, I ended up guild master.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.41,0:11:34.08,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And the next thing I learned was,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.08,0:11:38.29,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,strangely, the nights we spent excited over \Nstupid stuff were the nights we excelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.50,0:11:42.43,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Some of my companions were healthy. \NSome were sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.86,0:11:46.18,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And a lot of them had problems, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.13,0:11:49.93,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I learned that all of them were like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.68,0:11:53.18,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I started to care about my companions' lives,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.18,0:11:55.69,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and what they wanted me to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.28,0:11:59.36,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And I learned to be open-minded and ask others
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.36,0:12:00.94,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,for their opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:06.75,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That was after my companions had \Nlearned to deal with my temper.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.84,0:12:11.42,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Most raid guilds don't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.93,0:12:15.31,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you get an item as the result of a raid,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.31,0:12:17.71,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,you don't know who it belongs to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.35,0:12:21.19,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Some members aren't happy with what they get.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.54,0:12:25.57,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Some only care about what's in it for them,\Nand relationships are ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.11,0:12:30.80,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But we learned to talk with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.46,0:12:34.68,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I told my companions everything honestly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.68,0:12:38.48,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and they forgave my short temper and trusted me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.39,0:12:43.02,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And the name, Silver Sword,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.02,0:12:49.37,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,spread throughout {\i0}Elder Tale{\i1} as one \Nof the up-and-coming raid guilds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.73,0:12:59.82,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,So I understand that it feels \Nlike we're finished now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.26,0:13:01.90,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Like it's game over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.90,0:13:04.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like this is the real end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:06.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And it may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.64,0:13:08.26,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It may be, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.57,0:13:10.44,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When I came to this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.91,0:13:12.52,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,to be honest, I was happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.18,0:13:16.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You all were a little bit, as well, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.43,0:13:21.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No one here was one-hundred-percent unhappy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:26.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Because... This world is {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0}, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.21,0:13:29.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The world that we became almost \Nstupidly obsessed with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.33,0:13:32.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The world of the raids that we \Nwere better at than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.79,0:13:36.62,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Here, we thought, we might be able to make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.38,0:13:38.29,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,William!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.67,0:13:39.54,Default - flashback,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Guild master!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.83,0:13:41.72,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.26,0:13:44.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But more than any of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.10,0:13:47.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I was happy to be with you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:50.13,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You were all just like in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.68,0:13:52.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, so was I, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.72,0:13:54.18,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't matter, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:13:57.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We could do raids together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.59,0:14:00.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No one in this world would make fun of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.76,0:14:07.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But that means that, even if \Nwe lose, we don't run!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.79,0:14:09.28,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We may not be able to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.67,0:14:11.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We probably won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.08,0:14:14.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Odds are, we'll lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:16.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't run.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.93,0:14:19.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There are some things you can't just accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.06,0:14:22.71,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, if we go back, then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:24.05,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What would we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.57,0:14:27.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you take this from us, what's left?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.96,0:14:31.80,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We played {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0} so much that \Nothers thought we were weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.30,0:14:35.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've spent these last two years on {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.94,0:14:38.51,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I thought about it from morning to night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.19,0:14:42.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Eating, sleeping, bathing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.67,0:14:44.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Everything was for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.41,0:14:49.32,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even my studying was for {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.65,0:14:51.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.79,0:14:55.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to call me a vegetable, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.58,0:14:57.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a weirdo gamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.59,0:15:01.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so unsuited for society, \NI can spend a whole evening
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.23,0:15:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,overjoyed over a rare item!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.18,0:15:05.09,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's how serious I've been about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.48,0:15:11.43,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But that means that I can't run from \Ntwo or three extra raid bosses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.43,0:15:14.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I ran, where would I go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.07,0:15:17.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Will I run away and spend the rest \Nof my life making fun of games?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.94,0:15:20.25,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If I stop raiding, can I make friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.58,0:15:23.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Can I laugh and say, "Yeah, \Nthat was a waste of time"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.36,0:15:26.36,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Screw that crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.36,0:15:28.11,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.50,0:15:33.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're telling us to keep \Ndying instead of running?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.88,0:15:37.35,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do I have to go through that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.71,0:15:39.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Demikas...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.17,0:15:42.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If we have some way to win, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.95,0:15:45.81,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't. Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.33,0:15:49.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're just playing a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.32,0:15:52.33,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Even in a different world, that doesn't change.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.33,0:15:56.38,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're useless mouths to feed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.94,0:15:59.89,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And we can't even win the game we play.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.68,0:16:04.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Will you still tell us not to run?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.63,0:16:12.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I ran once...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.64,0:16:16.70,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It was bothering me, but I finally figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.27,0:16:21.29,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It was the first Round Table \Nconference in Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.89,0:16:25.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, I wanted to do \Nraids in this new world
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.59,0:16:27.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.57,0:16:30.15,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not wasting my time with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.50,0:16:32.07,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The safety of the city?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.07,0:16:33.78,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,That's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.19,0:16:35.93,Default - flashback,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:39.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I thought they were fools,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.30,0:16:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wasting their time on an impossible task.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.29,0:16:46.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I did something so horrible that, \Nif someone had done it to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.66,0:16:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would've wanted to punch them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.82,0:16:50.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.22,0:16:51.64,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I know that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.64,0:16:52.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.43,0:16:55.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I ignored them because I \Ndidn't think it would work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.89,0:17:00.45,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But there was one player who didn't run.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.47,0:17:02.69,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He was
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.54,0:17:05.33,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,the man I looked up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.69,0:17:10.11,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The legendary party who'd gone \Ntoe-to-toe with the best,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.11,0:17:13.25,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,on the toughest quests, without ever \Nmaking a guild of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.46,0:17:18.14,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Debauchery Tea Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.71,0:17:21.69,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard the rumors of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.69,0:17:26.40,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to dream that, someday, \Nthey would let me in, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.63,0:17:32.10,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But before I hit level 90, they split up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.68,0:17:34.58,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The members went back to being solo,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.58,0:17:37.24,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,without forming a guild, and split up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.00,0:17:43.00,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't understand why they'd left their \Nlegend if they were just going to quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.77,0:17:49.74,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There was a raid that I thought was pointless, \Nimpossible, and unwinnable, but he...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.77,0:17:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Shiroe won it, and made Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.04,0:17:56.12,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A raid that created a city!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.12,0:17:57.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,How can you make fun of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.96,0:18:00.01,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he was an incredible leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.30,0:18:01.51,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.51,0:18:04.72,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I... I looked up to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.09,0:18:06.72,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't just be an ordinary guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.17,0:18:10.02,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And when he came to me for a favor,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.02,0:18:12.50,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I was so happy, I agreed instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.50,0:18:14.84,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it would be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.23,0:18:17.66,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The villain in glasses brought it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.44,0:18:21.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Of course something horrible \Nwould happen to all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.20,0:18:26.47,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,He's a nuisance and a sadist. \NYou can see it by looking at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.36,0:18:30.19,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought it was fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.77,0:18:32.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I hoped we'd win.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.37,0:18:34.46,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The reason was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.46,0:18:37.45,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,because we're gamers, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.20,0:18:46.68,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.92,0:18:50.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I could give it one more go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.19,0:19:27.35,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm seriously an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.02,0:19:30.71,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.60,0:19:33.80,Default - italics,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,No... I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.54,0:19:36.68,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to give my friends victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.63,0:19:41.63,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,A guild master, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.63,0:19:46.74,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.17,0:19:48.37,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You awake?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.25,0:19:51.00,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.01,0:20:04.55,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,This is a good guild, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.18,0:20:06.10,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.43,0:20:08.58,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Could I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.21,0:20:11.27,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Could I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.13,0:20:14.33,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If Minori and Tohya were sad...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.33,0:20:16.33,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If Isuzu and Rudy were crying...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.15,0:20:21.02,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Could I cheer them up with \Nhonest words like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.26,0:20:24.24,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If Akatsuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.73,0:20:26.85,Default - flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.40,0:20:29.50,Default - flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's my job to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.94,0:20:32.52,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I want to help them win.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.61,0:20:35.23,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you, Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.64,0:20:37.63,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You know just what to say, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.99,0:20:40.38,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a top idol, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.66,0:20:47.53,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,So, do you have an idea, strategist?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.07,0:20:50.39,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I need to tell you something, Naotsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.28,0:20:52.52,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You, too, Tetra.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.80,0:20:55.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And William. And everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.14,0:20:58.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,About why we need this raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.82,0:21:00.67,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What waits down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.67,0:21:03.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Why I want the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.87,0:21:05.72,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I should have told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.51,0:21:09.42,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I took advantage of you, \Nand I tried to do it all myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.16,0:21:13.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If you'll let me, I have a plan that's a bit better.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.36,0:21:16.50,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But only a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.89,0:21:18.05,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,What are our odds?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.43,0:21:21.67,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Fifteen percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.70,0:21:24.05,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Good enough for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:25.55,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.92,0:21:29.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And I need to tell Kinjou and the others, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:31.21,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.58,0:21:33.06,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,About the land of Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.04,0:21:36.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I have to look them \Nin the eye and tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.68,0:21:42.75,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.75,0:21:44.34,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be back as soon as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.70,0:21:45.82,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.82,0:21:49.08,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have some New Year's soup with chicken waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.08,0:21:51.58,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's a promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.95,0:21:54.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a week since then. \NEverything is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.53,0:21:57.33,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We're about to go to the last battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.79,0:21:59.84,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to get that New Year's \Nsoba another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.38,0:22:03.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Tell the chief we'll be back by January 7th.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.49,0:22:06.88,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I need to tell you all something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.34,0:22:08.39,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.90,0:22:10.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.10,0:22:11.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.92,0:22:14.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come back to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.34,0:22:19.73,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this, people!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.11,0:22:23.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go plant our flag!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.25,0:22:28.24,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.74,0:22:31.45,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.66,0:22:33.64,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.18,0:24:09.92,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three, four.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.53,0:24:11.72,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The count sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.72,0:24:13.43,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Three raid bosses.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.43,0:24:14.68,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Preparations are complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.03,0:24:16.18,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Weapons in their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.18,0:24:17.44,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Maps in their eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.44,0:24:18.97,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The plan in their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.42,0:24:21.38,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Their odds of winning are fifteen percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.58,0:24:24.65,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,But their comrades are with them to try again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:26.23,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Retry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.65,0:24:30.94,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Retry
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.65,0:24:28.76,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Rise up once more.
